g ≠ 0 because ∇×(M×B) breaks up-down symmetry.
g ∝ (μᵣ-1)²/(μᵣ+1) × k_c × (B²-B_c²)/B_c²... sign depends on χ.
For χ=3: g < 0 → subcritical bifurcation, hysteresis at onset.
Hexagons selected because resonant triad k₁+k₂+k₃=0 provides quadratic coupling.
```

